Visualize output of BAWR Parameter Tests

library(dplyr)
library(tidyr)
library(ggplot2)

Load functions

read.snpreport <- function(filename){
    dat<-read.delim(filename, header=T)
    polydat <- filter(dat, dat$n_snps>0)
    fixeddat <- filter (dat, dat$n_snps==0)
    returndat <- list("alldata"=dat, "polymorphic"=polydat, "fixed"=fixeddat)
    return(returndat)
}

sum.snpreport <- function(filename){
  dat<-read.delim(filename, header=T)
  grouped.dat <- dat %>% group_by(m,M,n)
  sum.loci <- summarise(grouped.dat, total_loci=sum(n_loci)) #all loci
  sum.loci$poly <- summarise(filter(grouped.dat, n_snps > 0), total_loci=sum(n_loci))$total_loci  #polymorphic loci
  sum.loci$pct.poly <- sum.loci$poly/sum.loci$total_loci
  sum.loci$max.snps <- summarize(grouped.dat, snps=max(n_snps))$snps

  
  lilmrange <- unique(sum.loci$m)
  bigmrange <- unique(sum.loci$M)
  lilnrange <- unique(sum.loci$n)
  toreturn <- list("sumofloci"=sum.loci, "lilmrange"=lilmrange, "bigmrange"=bigmrange, "lilnrange"=lilnrange)
  return(toreturn)
}

select.dat <- function(dat, lilm=NA, bigm=NA, liln=NA){
  if(is.na(lilm)){
    lilm <- dat$lilmrange
  }
  if(is.na(bigm)){
    bigm <- dat$bigmrange
  }
  if(is.na(liln)){
    liln <- dat$lilnrange
  }
  sub.dat <- filter(dat$sumofloci, m %in% lilm & M %in% bigm & n %in% liln)
  return(sub.dat)
}

Load infiles

infile <- "BAWR_snpsperlocuspostfilt.txt"
fulldat <- read.snpreport(infile)
summeddat <- sum.snpreport(infile)
alldata <- select.dat(summeddat)  # Didn't make any selection, so this is 
                                  # all data but selecting just that part of the
                                  # summeddat object
                                  # alt alldata <- summeddat$sumofloci
re_dat<- alldata %>% gather("type","n_loci", 4:5)
re_dat$typemn <- paste(re_dat$type, "_m", re_dat$m, "_n", re_dat$n, sep="")

Plots

Plot number of total and polymorphic loci at different M, split by n and m

p<-ggplot(re_dat, aes(M, n_loci, by=typemn, color=as.factor(n))) + 
  geom_point(aes(col=as.factor(m))) + geom_path()
p <- p + labs(title="Total and Poly Loci at each M", y="No. of Loci", x="M")
p

### Plot Percentage Loci at each SNP Use original function to load all the data

dat<- fulldat$alldata
mysum <- dat %>% group_by(M,m,n) %>% mutate(pct = n_loci/sum(n_loci))
mysum$id <- paste("m",mysum$m,"_n", mysum$n, sep="")
mysum$id <- factor(mysum$id, c("m3_n1","m4_n1", "m5_n1",
                               "m3_n2","m4_n2", "m5_n2"))
p <- ggplot(mysum, aes(n_snps, pct, fill=factor(M))) + 
  facet_wrap(~id) +
  geom_bar(aes(fill=factor(M)),stat="identity", position="dodge", na.rm=T) + 
  theme_bw() + 
  scale_x_continuous(limits=c(-0.5,10), breaks=0:10)
p
